 Here is the HTML code for the webpage you requested, which contains information about resources and assistance available to residents of Amber Valley for managing their homes and energy costs:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Home Energy Advice - Amber Valley Borough Council</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">
    <!-- Additional stylesheet -->
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        /* Mobile navigation styles */
        .sideNavigation {
            display: none;
            width: 250px;
            position: absolute;
            height: 100%;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            padding-top: 60px;
            background-color: #f7f7f7;
            overflow-x: hidden;
            transition: 0.5s;
        }

        /* Open the side navigation when the user clicks on the menu icon */
        .open {
            width: 250px;
        }

        /* Style the header and the content */
        .header,
        .content {
            padding: 80px;
            height: 100%;
        }

        /* Style the main content */
        .main-content {
            margin-left: 250px;
        }

        /* Responsive layout - when the screen is less than 768px wide, make the side navigation show up on top of the content */
        @media screen and (max-width: 767px) {
            .sideNavigation {
                position: relative;
                margin-top: 70px;
            }
        }

        /* Sidebar for small screens - using the "reveal" technique */
        @media screen and (max-width: 767px) {
            .sideNavigation a {
                display: block;
                padding: 20px 25px;
                font-size: 18px;
            }

            .sideNavigation a.active {
                background-color: #f4511e;
                color: white;
            }

            .sideNavigation a:hover,
            .sideNavigation .active {
                padding-left: 0;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <!-- Mobile navigation button -->
    <div id="mySidebar" class="sideNavigation">
        <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="closebtn" onclick="closeNav()">&times;</a>
        <!-- Navigation menu -->
        <div class="hidden-xs">
            <span class="list-group-item list-group-header">Navigation menu</span>
            <a href="/" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action"><span aria-hidden="true">&lt; </span>Back to Home</a>
            <a href="/housing/" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action"><span aria-hidden="true">&lt; </span>Back to Housing</a>
            <a href="/housing/home-energy-advice/" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action active"><span aria-hidden="true">&lt; </span>Back to Home energy advice</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="header">
        <button class="openbtn" onclick="openNav()">&#9776;</button>
        <h1>HOME ENERGY ADVICE - AMBER VALLEY BOROUGH COUNCIL</h1>
    </header>

    <!-- Main content -->
    <div class="content">
        <div class="main-content">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8 col-sm-6 col-xs-12" style="margin: auto;">
                        <!-- Content -->
                        <h3>Resources and assistance for home energy advice in Amber Valley</h3>
                        <p>Here you will find information about resources and assistance available to residents of Amber Valley to help manage their homes and energy costs.</p>

                        <h4>Warm Homes Health Programme (WHHP)</h4>
                        <p>The Warm Homes Health Programme is a collaborative initiative led by Derbyshire County Council that aims to prevent cold-related illnesses, such as flu and pneumonia. You can register for the programme if you are aged 65 or over, have a long-term health condition, receive one of the following benefits: Income Support, Jobseeker's Allowance (Income-based), Employment and Support Allowance (Income-related), Pension Credit Guarantee, Housing Benefit for people who are retired, or have a low household income.</p>
                        <p><a href="https://www.derbyshire.gov.uk/community/cost-of-living/warmhomeshealthprogramme.aspx" target="_blank">Learn more about the Warm Homes Health Programme</a></p>

                        <h4>Emergency Assistance Fund (EAF)</h4>
                        <p>The EAF is a grant scheme that provides additional financial support to vulnerable households struggling with fuel bills or other essential household costs. To be eligible for the EAF, you must meet certain criteria.</p>
                        <p><a href="https://www.derbyshire.gov.uk/community/cost-of-living/emergencyassistancefund.aspx" target="_blank">Learn more about the Emergency Assistance Fund</a></p>

                        <h4>Other Energy-Related Grants and Schemes</h4>
                        <p>There are several energy-related grants and schemes available for households in Amber Valley, designed to help reduce home energy costs.</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><a href="https://www.derbyshire.gov.uk/community/cost-of-living/grants.aspx" target="_blank">Home Energy Efficiency Grants</a></li>
                            <li><a href="https://www.stwater.co.uk/my-account/help-when-you-need-it/big-difference-scheme" target="_blank">Big Difference Scheme by Severn Trent Water</a></li>
                            <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/the-warm-home-discount-scheme" target="_blank">Warm Home Discount Scheme</a></li>
                        </ul>

                        <!-- Useful links -->
                        <h4>Other useful resources and contacts</h4>
                        <div class="lgLinkContainer">
                            <ul>
                                <li><a href="https://www.derbyshire.gov.uk/community/cost-of-living/cost-of-living.aspx" target="_blank">Derbyshire County Council - cost of living</a></li>
                                <li class="furtherHelp">Need further help or information?</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <p><a href="mailto:eh-housing@ambervalley.gov.uk">Contact the team directly on 01773 841335 or email eh-housing@ambervalley.gov.uk</a></p>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Sidebar for small screens -->
                    <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-6 col-xs-12 hidden-lg hidden-md">
                        <div class="sideNavigation  hidden-print">
                            <span class="list-group-item list-group-header">Navigation menu</span>
                            <a href="/" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action"><span aria-hidden="true">&lt; </span>Back to Home</a>
                            <a href="/housing/" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action"><span aria-hidden="true">&lt; </span>Back to Housing</a>
                            <a href="/housing/home- energy-advice/" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action active"><span aria-hidden="true">&lt; </span>Back to Home energy advice</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- JavaScript for mobile navigation -->
    <script>
        function openNav() {
            document.getElementById("mySidebar").style.width = "250px";
            document.getElementById("mySidebar").className += " open";
        }

        function closeNav() {
            document.getElementById("mySidebar").style.width = "0";
            document.getElementById("mySidebar").className =
                "sideNavigation";
        }
    </script>

</body>

</html>
```
